  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "24c4750c-f3ba-80de-b795-dc34f3bf90a4",
      "heading": "Summary Table PRED",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Moment of Prediction",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "End of Course Grade",
          "At-risk (C, D, F) vs Not at-risk (A, B)",
          "220 PT students, 270DSP students",
          "3 editions of 1 Program Theorry I and 1 Digital Signal PRocesing Course, respectively",
          "LMS logs. E-Book system",
          "[Attendance, RReport Submission, Course Accesses, E-book reading time, Highlights in E-Books, Notes  in E-Book, Total Actions in E-Book, Word Count in E-Portfolio]",
          "Every Week",
          "Authors extract data from  Moodle and the BookRoll systems. \n\nQuizzes were not considered for the experiment. Information is represented as a vector for every week.\n\nThe logs are converted into Active Learner Points on the different topics for each week. ALP is a score between 0 and 5 that is distribution-based.\n\nThis is subsequently given as input a to the weighted attention. The weighting occurs both at a feature and temporal dimensions.\n\n\n\n",
          "MLP, LSTM, GRU, Attn-ANN",
          "30-Repeated Holdout Method (90/10)",
          "Week 1:\nPT\n{F1-Score: 0.402 - LSTM, Accuracy: 0.551 - MLP, AUC: 0.607 - GRU}\n\nWeek 3\nPT\n{F1-Score: 0.543 - Attn-ANN, Accuracy: 0.617- Attn-ANN, AUC: 0.737 - Attn-ANN}\n\nDSP\n{F1-Score: 0.713 - Attn-ANN, Accuracy: 0.819 - Attn-ANN, , AUC: 0.867 - Attn-ANN}\n\nWeek 5\nPT\n{F1-Score: 0.601 - GRU, Accuracy: 0.665- Attn-ANN, AUC: 0.822 - Attn-ANN}\n\nDSP\n{F1-Score: 0.761 - Attn-ANN, Accuracy: 0.862 - Attn-ANN, , AUC: 0.903 - Attn-ANN}\n\nWeek 7\nPT\n{F1-Score: 0.607 - Attn-ANN, Accuracy: 0.643 - Attn-ANN, AUC: 0.739 - Attn-ANN}\n\nDSP\n{F1-Score: 0.806 - GRU, Accuracy: 0.862 - Attn-ANN, , AUC: 0.912 - GRU}",
          "The authors do a new approach to student performance prediction using a temporal representation with Attention Weighting on both a time and feature dimension level. \n\nThe authors compare their approach against other sequence-based approaches (LSTM, GRU). The results show that it is possible to obtain good results by the Courses’ Halfway Point. \n\nSurprisingly, this approach seems to exhibit some diminishing returns (model eprformance does not significantly increase past a certain point in time).  \n\nAblation studies show that the approach seems to generate better results than using the time or the feature dimension separately. \n\nThe time dimension alone also does, on occasion, outperform both modules.",
          "- Small and unbalanced dataset\n\nDifficult to generalize to other educational outside Informatics\n\n- Availability of Data from Moodle and BookRoll\n\n- Does not consider other additional sources of data.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
